### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@email = dev@zenecho.com
@password = Password123!
@name = Dev ZenEcho

### 1. Register User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "{{name}}"
}

### 2. Login User
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Save Tokens from response
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.data.refreshToken}}

### 3. Get User Profile (Protected - Requires Access Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4. Refresh Tokens (Requires Refresh Token)
# @name refresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Authorization: Bearer {{refreshToken}}

### Save New Tokens
@newAccessToken = {{refresh.response.body.data.accessToken}}
@newRefreshToken = {{refresh.response.body.data.refreshToken}}

### 5. Get User Profile with New Access Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{newAccessToken}}

### 6. Logout User (Invalidates Refresh Token in DB)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{newAccessToken}}

### 7. Try to Refresh again (Should fail with 401 as token is revoked)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Authorization: Bearer {{newRefreshToken}}
